<html>
<body>
<h2>JavaScript can do following things:-</h2>
<p id="demo">JavaScript can change HTML content.</p>
<button type="button" onclick= 'document.getElementById("demo").innerHTML="Hello JavaScript!"'>Click Me!</button>
<br><br>
<button type="button" onclick= "document.getElementById('demo').innerHTML='Welcome'">Click Here!</button> 

<p> JavaScript can change HTML attribute values. <br>
In this case JavaScript changes the value of the src(source) attribute of an image.</p>
<button onclick="document.getElementById('myImage').src='Smiling_face.jpg'">Smile</button>
<img id="myImage" src="Smiling_large.png" style="width:100px">
<button onclick="document.getElementById('myImage').src='Smiling_large.png'">Be Happy</button>

<p id="demo1">JavaScript can change the style of an HTML element.</p>
<button type="button" onclick="document.getElementById('demo1').style.fontSize='20px'">Click</button>

<p>JavaScript can hide HTML elements.</p>
<p id="demo2"> Hello JS</p>
<button type="button" onclick="document.getElementById('demo2').style.display='none'">Hide</button>

<p>JavaScript can show hidden HTML elements.</p>
<button type="button" onclick="document.getElementById('demo2').style.display='block'">Show</button>


</body>
</html>